summary:
Oh hello there!
Here&rsquo;s a true story for you. My friend once showed me a book and said &ldquo;My buddy published this collection of his own poetry.&rdquo; I thought &ldquo;Pshh, I could write a book, I bet it&rsquo;s not that hard.&rdquo;
Two years later, here I am, fully lacking any published books. I&rsquo;ll admit that maybe it&rsquo;s harder to write a novel than I had initially thought. While it takes maybe ten hours to read a book, it turns out it takes a bit longer to actually write one.
